The paper deals with the problem of scheduling data packets over an unreliable channel to minimize estimation error, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of a remote linear estimator and a constant Kalman gain suggests a focus on control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the value of information and prioritizing packet transmissions, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
